articles.title: Introduction to JavaScript
articles.body: JavaScript is a versatile language used primarily for web development.

articles.title: Understanding React
articles.body: React is a JavaScript library for building user interfaces, maintained by Facebook.

articles.title: Getting Started with Node.js
articles.body: Node.js allows you to run JavaScript on the server side and build scalable network applications.

articles.title: What is an API?
articles.body: An API (Application Programming Interface) allows different software systems to communicate with each other.

articles.title: Benefits of TypeScript
articles.body: TypeScript adds static typing to JavaScript, making it easier to catch errors early in development.

articles.title: CSS Flexbox Guide
articles.body: Flexbox is a layout model in CSS that makes it easier to design flexible responsive layout structures.

articles.title: Responsive Web Design
articles.body: Responsive design ensures that web pages look good on all devices, from desktops to smartphones.

articles.title: Using Git for Version Control
articles.body: Git is a distributed version control system that helps developers collaborate and track changes in their code.

articles.title: Understanding RESTful APIs
articles.body: RESTful APIs follow a set of rules for creating web services that are scalable and easy to use.

articles.title: Deploying Applications with Docker
articles.body: Docker allows you to package applications into containers, making deployment more consistent and efficient.
